==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coincide
<hw>Co`in*cide"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Coincided</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Coinciding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>co-</ets> +
<ets>incidere</ets> to fall on; <ets>in + cadere</ets> to fall: cf. F.
<ets>co⟦ium⟧ncider</ets>. See <er>Chance</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To occupy the same place in space, as two equal
triangles, when placed one on the other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If the equator and the ecliptic had <qex>coincided</qex>, it would
have rendered the annual revoluton of the earth useless.</q>
<rj><qau>Cheyne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To occur at the same time; to be contemporaneous;
<as>as, the fall of Granada <ex>coincided</ex> with the discovery of
America</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To correspond exactly; to agree; to concur; <as>as,
our aims <ex>coincide</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rules of right jugdment and of good ratiocination often
<qex>coincide</qex> with each other.</q> <rj><qau>Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coincidence</ent>⟦br⟧
